ZH: 我昨天睡得很早。
EN: I went to bed very early yesterday.

ZH: 他睡得很熟。
EN: He sleeps deeply.

ZH: 她昨晚没睡好。
EN: She didn't sleep well last night.

ZH: 他睡了一整天。
EN: He slept all day.

ZH: 我很困，想睡觉。
EN: I'm very tired and want to sleep.

ZH: 你看起来很累，去睡一觉吧。
EN: You look tired, go take a nap.

ZH: 昨天下午我在办公桌上睡着了。
EN: I fell asleep at my desk yesterday afternoon.

ZH: 他今天早上睡过头了，要迟到了。
EN: He overslept this morning and will be late.

ZH: 她在课堂上睡着了。
EN: She fell asleep in class.

ZH: 我尽量晚睡一点。
EN: I try to sleep in a bit later.

ZH: 她不太能睡在别人家。
EN: She can't sleep at other people's houses.

ZH: 我每天晚上都睡觉前读书。
EN: I read before bed every night.

ZH: 他看电视看睡着了。
EN: He fell asleep while watching TV.

ZH: 我想拍个小盹，可是睡不着。
EN: I want to take a nap but can't fall asleep.

ZH: 他感冒了，不能睡好。
EN: He has a cold and can't sleep well.

ZH: 妈妈说这件事要着急着急就睡不着了。
EN: Mom said if you worry too much, you won't be able to sleep.

ZH: 我昨天心情不好，晚上一夜都没睡。
EN: I was in a bad mood yesterday and didn’t sleep all night.

ZH: 下午茶过后小睡一下，会舒服很多。
EN: Taking a short nap after afternoon tea will be very comfortable.

ZH: 我最喜欢的事情就是躺在床上睡午觉。
EN: My favorite thing is to lay in bed and take a nap.

ZH: 她喜欢熬夜睡不好。
EN: She likes to stay up late and has trouble sleeping.
